Colombian Stock Movers: Coltejer, Pacific Rubiales Energy Gain

-- B y   B l a k e   S c h m i d t
-- 
2011-10-14T20:07:51Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-10-14/colombian-stock-movers-coltejer-pacific-rubiales-energy-gain.html
The following companies had unusual
price changes in Bogota trading. Stock symbols are in
parentheses and prices are as of 3 p.m. local time.  The IGBC Index rose 0.4 percent to 13,355.48 while the
Colcap Index gained 0.4 percent to 1,618.42.  Coltejer SA (COLTEJ)  , a Colombian clothing maker and
exporter, rose 1 percent to 1.01 pesos. President Barack Obama
may sign bills for free-trade agreements with  South Korea ,
 Colombia  and Panama after they were approved by U.S. lawmakers
Oct. 12.  Pacific Rubiales Energy Corp. (PRE)  , the Toronto-based
oil producer that operates fields in Colombia, rose 0.7 percent
to 44,700 pesos, a three-week high. The company agreed to buy 19
percent of outstanding shares in CGX Energy Inc., a Toronto-
based exploration company with blocks in Guyana, for $41
million, according to a statement on its website late yesterday.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Blake Schmidt in Bogota at 
 bschmidt16@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
David Papadopoulos at 
 papadopoulos@bloomberg.net  